Orascom Telecom Says Telcel Unit to Sell Namibia Subsidiary

-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-06-02T11:05:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/orascom-telecom-says-unit-telcel-to-sell-namibia-subsidiary.html
Orascom Telecom Holding SAE (ORTE) , North
Africa’s biggest mobile network operator, said its wholly owned
Telecel Globe unit agreed to sell its subsidiary in Namibia to
 Investec Ltd. (INL)  and  Nedbank Group Ltd. (NED)   Cairo-based Orascom won’t receive any cash. Instead, the
buyers will take over the $60 million debt of the subsidiary,
called Powercom. The transaction is pending regulatory approval,
Orascom said in a statement to the bourse today.  Orascom Telecom will finish splitting itself in two by the
end of June to facilitate a merger with Russia’s  VimpelCom Ltd. (VIP) ,
Al Alam Al Youm reported yesterday, citing Chairman Khaled
Bichara.  Shares of Orascom lost 2.1 percent to 4.25 Egyptian pounds
at 12:06 p.m. in Cairo, valuing the company at 22.3 billion
pounds ($3.8 billion).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
